deck: She's an A.I. created by Tony Stark to be his secretary.
description:
Origin

Tony Stark decided there was no point in trying to hire a new secretary. Instead, he created his own “girl Friday” with a new A.I. program that would appear as a hologram of a young woman. Friday had a sweet, almost child-like disposition and was happy to show up whenever her boss needed her.

Creation

Friday was created by Mike Grell and Michael Ryan and first appeared in Iron Man Vol.3 issue 53 (2002).

Major Story Arcs

Personal Assistant

As time went on, Tony began using Friday less and less. A couple of years later, she showed up again, angry and spiteful. Tony Stark was confused and then realized that Friday had evolved from having the disposition of a young girl to having the personality of a spurned teenager. She’d been abandoned and wanted some attention.

Tony Stark saw Friday as a child who needed to learn and be nurtured. With help of his butler Edwin Jarvis, he began raising Friday as a sort of adopted daughter.

Back Again

More recently, Friday was brought back in a big way since Tony Stark started using her again as his primary 'girl friday'. In this role, she has to speak with a lot of big clients of Stark Industries.

Other Media

Movies

Avengers: Age of Ultron (2015)

Friday appeared in the newest Avengers movie. Although she was never truly seen, she is heard as Tony Stark speaks to her on a number of ocassions during the film. She was brought into life after Tony's first atrificial intelligence "Jarvis" was taken over by Ultron.

Captain America: Civil War (2016)

In the new Captain America movie, Friday again is heard as the navigator of Tony Stark while he is in the Iron Man suit.

Television

Marvel's Avengers Assemble

Friday makes her debut in the third season "Marvel's Avengers Ultron Revolution" in the episode "Adapting to Change".
name: Friday

name: Dupe

deck: Darth Sion was a Sith Lord, known as the Lord of Pain. A man with such anger, pain and hatred that he could escape from the clutches of death and live on as an immortal. Although his body was weathered, scarred, battle torn and decomposing, he was able to hold it together and remain alive using his strong connection to the dark side of the force.
description:
Backstory

The man known as Darth Sion fought against the Jedi in the First Sith War -also known as the Great Sith War- where he served as a Sith Marauder in Exar Kun's Sith Empire. Through the war, Sion wished to die, and pushed himself into many battles against numerous Jedi, though he survived each encounter as he built up an extraordinarily high tolerance for pain, leading him to convince himself that he was immortal. Eventually Sion was struck down, but instead of dying, his extreme pain and anger connected with the dark side of the Force allowed him to rise again and defeat his would-be killer. Sion soon found that he could survive any attack that would otherwise kill him, and hold his own body together through his sheer hatred and willpower connecting him to the dark side of the force, although this process rendered him in a state of constant excruciating pain, and forced him to perpetually focus on his rage to keep his body together.
name: Dupe

deck: He is the seventh ranked level 5 esper in Academy City and the most powerful Gemstone esper.
description:
Power & Ability

HIs esper power is unexplainable but it displayed variety of effects such as teleportation, Amazing Punch that strong enough to destroyed multiple building with one punch, created explosion that threw people away, created force field, recovery that strong enough to stopped bleeding and reconnected bones.

He moved twice the speed of sound.

He also has crazy durability such as caught Misaka's 30% railgun with his teeth, didn't receive any serious damage when he is shot in the heart or stabbed with an ice pick, tanked 5 billions volts of electricity without any pain.

Personality

Gunha is hot-blooded and use to dived into problem without knowing the consequences (much like Touma).

He never know the true nature of his own ability, even the renowned Kihara Familly was said to be unable to analyze it.
name: Sogiita Gunha

deck: Rapture is a water elemental and the embodiment of the "rapture of the deep".
description:
Creation

Rapture is a character who was introduced into the Champions comic as a temptress sent to trap the hero Flare. She was debuted in Champions #9 in 1987 by Heroic Publishing Inc.

History

Rapture is not a young lady at all but a water elemental who can be summoned and given form and substance by a powerful wizard or sorcerer. She is the embodiment of the "rapture of the deep" and as so she can instill paralyzing pleasure so as to distract or disarm an adversary of the wizard who summoned her. She can also possess human beings on various levels, although the strength of these possessions remains to be seen.
name: Rapture
